Why each additional element is added
Load Balancer (HAProxy)

Added to distribute incoming requests across multiple servers.

Benefits:

Improves availability
Improves performance
Prevents a single web server from becoming overloaded
Allows one server to fail while the site remains available
Second Server

Added for redundancy and scalability.

Benefits:

Handles more traffic
Reduces risk of complete outage if one server fails
Allows maintenance on one server while another continues serving users
Database Replica

Added to provide redundancy for database data.

Benefits:

Backup copy of data
Can be promoted if the primary database fails
Can be used for read operations in larger infrastructures
Load Balancer Distribution Algorithm

A common HAProxy algorithm is Round Robin.

How it works:

Request 1 -> Server 1
Request 2 -> Server 2
Request 3 -> Server 1
Request 4 -> Server 2

Traffic is distributed evenly among available servers.

