In this design, the load balancer is typically configured in an Active-Active setup.

How a Primary-Replica Database Cluster Works
Primary (Master)

Responsible for:

INSERT
UPDATE
DELETE
Data modifications

All write operations occur on the Primary database.

Replica (Slave)

Receives updates from the Primary through replication.

Responsible for:

Maintaining a copy of the data
Optionally serving read queries

