Issues with this Infrastructure
SPOF (Single Point of Failure)

Even with improvements, some SPOFs remain:

Load Balancer
User
  |
HAProxy

If the single HAProxy server fails:

No requests can reach the web servers.
Primary Database

If the Primary database fails:

Write operations stop.
Users may be unable to create or update data.
Security Issues
No Firewall

Problems:

All services may be exposed directly to the Internet.
Increased attack surface.
No HTTPS

Problems:

Traffic is transmitted in plain text.
Credentials and sensitive information can be intercepted.
Vulnerable to man-in-the-middle attacks.
No Monitoring

Problems:

No visibility into server health.
Failures may go unnoticed.
Difficult troubleshooting.
No performance metrics or alerting.
Summary of Remaining Weaknesses
Load balancer is a SPOF.
Primary database is a SPOF for writes.
No firewall protection.
No HTTPS encryption.
No monitoring or alerting.
Database replication does not automatically provide failover.
